      "content": "thanks but i dont think it's just 'urban planning' guidelines. like, standard efficiency doesn't explain why certain occult-looking symbols seem to emerge when you connect the major axes of these locations. i've been mapping the sightlines specifically looking at how they intersect with older, non-commercial structures. if you look at the ley line theories or even just the way old initiatory societies used geometry, the overlap between these two specific cities is too heavy to be just \"traffic flow.\" look at the way the specific spire of St. Paul's aligns with the coordinates of certain monuments in NYC... it's almost like a signature. do you see how that pattern fits into something much older than modern city planning?",
